The research council says it has put together 72 teams of trained field workers who will be dispatched countrywide. JOHANNESBURG The Human Sciences Research Council has officially launched South Africa s fifth HIV and Health study.It has announced it will be visiting 60,000 households across the country to ask individuals to take part in the survey.The research council says it has put together 72 teams of trained field workers who will be dispatched countrywide.Deputy executive director Geoffrey Setswe says the survey will be conducted over the next seven to nine months. This is a national population-based survey. We are going into households to check the prevalence and incidents of HIV/Aids. We want to see how big the epidemic is and whether the epidemic is growing or not. (Edited by Neo Koza)